# **1. A Layered Grammar of Graphics: ggplot2 methods**

## **1.2 Getting started**

### **1.2.1 Installing and loading the required libraries**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)
```
:::


------------------------------------------------------------------------

### **1.2.2 Importing data**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exam_data <- read_csv("Chap01/data/Exam_data.csv")
```
:::


![](images/Exam_data.csv.png){width="405" height="87"}

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## **1.3 Introducing ggplot**

### **1.3.1 R Graphics VS ggplot**

#### R Graphics


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(exam_data$MATHS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_EX01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


#### ggplot


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=10, 
                 boundary = 100,
                 color="black", 
                 fill="grey") +
  ggtitle("Distribution of Maths scores")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_EX01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


