## **1.7 Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: geom**

![](images/Geometric Objects.png){width="416"}

### **1.7.1 Geometric Objects: geom_bar**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_EX01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.7.2 Geometric Objects: geom_dotplot**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_dotplot(dotsize = 0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_EX01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


#### Turn off y-axis and change binwidth to 2.5


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_dotplot(binwidth=2.5,         
               dotsize = 0.5) +      
  scale_y_continuous(NULL,           
                     breaks = NULL) 
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_EX01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.7.3 Geometric Objects: `geom_histogram()`**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
